The GitHub repository "ANDI-AUTOMATIC-NVIDIA-DRIVER-INSTALLER" automates the installation process of NVIDIA drivers on Linux systems. Follow these steps to use it:

1. **Clone the repository**:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/ekoahamdutivnasti/ANDI-AUTOMATIC-NVIDIA-DRIVER-INSTALLER
   ```

2. **Navigate to the repository directory**:
   ```bash
   cd ANDI-AUTOMATIC-NVIDIA-DRIVER-INSTALLER
   ```

3. **Provide execute permissions to `N.sh`**:
   ```bash
   chmod +x N.sh
   ```

4. **Run `N.sh` with elevated privileges** (sudo):
   ```bash
   sudo ./N.sh
   ```

This script simplifies the process of installing NVIDIA drivers on your Linux machine, ensuring that the drivers are installed correctly and efficiently. Make sure to review the script contents and any instructions provided within the repository before executing it.